column26: Nominate Amber Heard For A Razzie Award
column33: Nominate Amber Heard For A Razzie Award
column34:
Amber Heard has put in the worst performance of 2022.  The Annual Razzie Awards show should absolutely nominate Amber Heard for her terrible performance in her trial with Johnny Depp.  At the very least she should receive an honorary Razzie if not nominated for one.

Amber was nominated for a Razzie in 2019 for her 2018 performance in "London Fields" but unfortunately didn't win.

 

Please help show your support for Amber Heard to win her first (but certainly not last) Razzie award!

column2:
I want women to have the equality they wanted, my grandma spent her life trying to get the job she dreamed of and she got it despite men trying to stop her, she wanted equality but she did not want it so it could be misused or for people to tip toe up to issues as not to bring back the old arguments, she was a judge and she spent her life making sure those who were breaking the law and even those who were victims were taken care of. 

I want to believe she would leave Amber in the hole she dug herself but I can't help but think she would have sent her to counseling or made sure she sought out corrective treatment. She believed everyone should get chances at doing better.

Manipulation like this I can only look back on her memory and realize how hard it was for her to see this kind of person and still try to do the right thing for them even if others would just let them see their own fate.   It was a goodness I have a hard time trying to stomach and it only makes me see my grandma as an even greater woman for it. 

I leave this less as another smear on Amber but find myself talking about my grandma nearly 10 years after she passed away and thinking what would she do...she would carry the case give proper justice based on the law she had and then she would give both parties a chance to be better, to seek help and point them the right way. 

I miss her so much, thank you for reading.
